put.description:
You can use the following request to replace translations for the specified category with the translations provided in the request.

     FieldType
     1 - Name
     2 - Description
            
     Actual request body example
    [
        {
            "dictionaryId": 3,
            "fieldType": 1,
            "value": "Test"
        },
        {
            "dictionaryId": 2,
            "fieldType": 2,
            "value": "test2"
        },
        {
            "dictionaryId": 3,
            "fieldType": 1,
            "value": "Test3"
        }, ...............
    ]
            
For every dictionary translation has both Name and Description, if one of them is not provided for dictionary, empty value will be saved instead.

get.description:
This endpoint supports OData filtering.<br />
You can use the following request to retrieve Likelihood of Approvals that match the specified filters.<br />
Example:

    api/workflow/v1/likelihoodOfApprovals?$filter=name like 'example'
    
The following attribute properties are available to OData, and they have a specific support for the $filter option.<br />

    name - $filter eq, ne, like
    
Additional OData options are available:

    $orderby={properties name} {desc/asc} {default on code property in ascending order}
    $top={number, max 1000}
    $skip={number}

This endpoint have specific support for $search option:<br /> 

    $search={some_value}
    Properties search by this option: name

The following properties are available for pagination: <br />
            
     $orderby={properties name} {desc/asc} (only producttypeid and producttypename)
     $top={number} {default is 10, max is 1000}
     $skip={number}

The following properties are available for pagination: <br />
            
     $top={number} {default is 10}
     $skip={number} {default is 0)

This endpoint supports OData ordering and pagination.<br />
    $orderby={properties columnName} {desc/asc}
    $top={default is 10, max is 1000}
    $skip={number} 
            
This endpoint has specific support for the $search option:<br /> 
            
    $search={some_value}
    You can use search option by fields: columnName, currency

post.description:
Use this endpoint to persist both visibility rules and filters at once.  
It will replace the existing configuration for the specified user type.  
            
Example:

    POST /api/quote/v1/configuration

Body:
{
  "userTypeId": 5,
  "columns": [
    { "columnName": "STATUS", "label": "Status" },
    { "columnName": "CURRENCY", "label": "Currency" }
  ],
  "filters": [
    { "columnName": "STATUS", "label": "Status", "operator": "StringContains", "isQuickSearch": false },
    { "columnName": "CURRENCY", "label": "Currency", "operator": "Equals", "isQuickSearch": true, "quickOperator": "Contains" }
  ]
}
